claim.claim-text:
1. A method of operating a base station in a wireless communication system, the method comprising:
receiving a data packet from a user equipment device via contention-based uplink access, the data packet comprising an identifier that uniquely identifies the user equipment device in the wireless communication system;
decoding the received data packet;
when the received data packet is correctly decoded,
receiving a buffer status report with the data packet, the buffer status report indicating an amount of data remaining to be transmitted by the user equipment device;
analyzing the buffer status report to determine the amount of data remaining to be transmitted by the user equipment device;
preparing an acknowledgment message such that its content is influenced by the amount of data remaining to be transmitted by the user equipment device;
sending the acknowledgment message to the user equipment device within a designated response window, the acknowledgment message comprising the identifier of the user equipment device, wherein the acknowledgement message is sent using a signaling channel between the base station and the user equipment device.

7. A method of operating a user equipment device in a wireless communication system, the method comprising:
identifying an amount of data to be transmitted from the user equipment device to a base station in the wireless communication system;
determining a next scheduled transmit time for dedicated access to the base station;
transmitting, using contention-based access to the base station, a data packet containing the identified amount of data when one of the time until the next scheduled transmit time is longer than a threshold amount of time and
only one resource allocation is required to accommodate all of the identified amount of data; and
transmitting, using scheduled dedicated access to the base station, a data packet containing at least some of the identified amount of data when both (a) the time until the next scheduled transmit time is shorter than the threshold amount of time and (b) the identified amount of data cannot be transmitted using only one resource allocation.
